Construct a PHP script to lower-case and upper-case, all elements in an array.

CODE:
<?php
$fruits = array("Apple", "Banana", "Cherry", "Mango");

// Convert all elements to lowercase
$lower = array_map("strtolower", $fruits);

// Convert all elements to uppercase
$upper = array_map("strtoupper", $fruits);

echo "Lowercase Array: ";
print_r($lower);

echo "<br>Uppercase Array: ";
print_r($upper);
?>

OUTPUT:
Lowercase Array: Array
(
    [0] => apple
    [1] => banana
    [2] => cherry
    [3] => mango
)
<br>Uppercase Array: Array
(
    [0] => APPLE
    [1] => BANANA
    [2] => CHERRY
    [3] => MANGO
)
